0:Peacetime
1:Our lieges got encircled while being on quite an open valley. The enemy decided to play with you a bit, giving us a head start before dancing to his flute. It is better not to think about the material of flute.
2:The preparation phase has begun. You have 35 seconds to release your troops before peacetime ends.
3:The market is on fire. You have to decide whether to save the market or to save time for settlement development. Market is not available for building.
4:Escaped workers from the burnt market join the building of your town.
5:"Very Hard" difficulty level||Only ashes remain after that fire, no one escaped.
6:"Very Hard" difficulty level||Sir Scout has bought the new flute of a new generation. When he has enough of that, he will blow the whistle with such power that everyone will know that peacetime is over.
7:You've committed an apostasy - you've equipped a scout.
8:"Very Hard" difficulty level||Sir Scout's … Scouts?.. told us that their troops return after 40 minutes. Or maybe not 40? Their speech was quite slurred.
